{% block submarine %}
    <table class="table table-bordered">
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Cost</strong></td>
            <td>6</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Attack</strong>
            </td>
            <td>2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Defense</strong>
            </td>
            <td>1</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Move</strong>
            </td>
            <td>2</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <h5>Unit Characteristics</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Surprise Strike: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Attacking and defending Submarines can conduct a Surprise Strike on step 2 of the General Combat Phase</li>
                <li>Each attacking submarine conducting a Surprise Strike rolls one die, hitting with a 2 or less for the attacking player, and with a 1 or less for the defending player</li>
                <li>For each hit, the attacked player takes one sea unit and moves it behind the casualty strip (undamaged capital ships are not removed, but take damage)</li>
                <li>Transports
                    can be chosen as casualties only if there are no other
                    eligible units. Submerged submarines can’t be chosen as
                    casualties since they have been removed from the battle</li>
                <li>Once all attacking and defending submarines that
                    conducted a Surprise Strike have fired, the generated casualties are removed from the game</li>
                <li>Submarines that submerged or fired on this step may not attack or defend on step 3 and 4 of the General Combat Phase</li>
                <li>Destroyers cancel this unit characteristic</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Submersible: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Can submerge to not participate in an upcoming battle. It is removed from the Battle Strip and returned to the game board in the contested sea zone</li>
                <li>Destroyers cancel this unit characteristic</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>On Station: </strong>Rolls 2 dice when disrupting a convoy</li>
        <li><strong>Treat Hostile Sea Zones as Friendly: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Can move through a sea zone that contains enemy units, either in combat or noncombat movement</li>
                <li>If it enters a sea zone containing an enemy destroyer, it must end its movement there. If it ends its combat move in a hostile sea zone, combat will occur.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Doesn’t Block Enemy Movement: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Any sea zone that contains only enemy submarines doesn’t stop the movement of a sea unit.</li>
                <li>Sea units ending their combat movement in a sea zone containing only enemy submarines may choose to attack them or not.</li>
                <li>Sea units can also end their noncombat movement in a sea zone containing only enemy submarines</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Can’t Hit Air Units: </strong>When attacking or defending,submarines can’t hit air units</li>
        <li><strong>Can’t Be Hit by Air Units: </strong>
        <ul>
            <li>When attacking or defending, hits scored by air units can’t be assigned to submarines</li>
            <li>Destroyers cancel this unit characteristic</li>
    </ul>
{% endblock %}

