    <h5>Unit Characteristics</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No Combat Value: </strong>Cannot fire in the defending units fire step, but can be taken as casualty. Can never attack.</li>
        <li><strong>Doesn’t Block Enemy Movement: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Any sea zone that contains only enemy transports doesn’t stop the movement of a sea unit.</li>
                <li>Sea units ending their combat movement in a sea zone containing only enemy transports automatically destroy all transports</li>
                <li>Sea units can also end their noncombat movement in a sea zone containing only enemy transports</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Chosen Last: </strong>Can be chosen as casualties only if there are no other eligible units</li>
        <li><strong>Carry Land Units: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Can carry land units belonging to you or to friendly powers</li>
                <li>Capacity: any 1 land unit, plus 1 additional infantry</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Loading and Offloading: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Can load units in friendly sea zones before, during, and after it moves</li>
                <li>It can offload in only one territory, and once it offloads, it can’t move, load, or offload again that turn.</li>
                <li>Cannot offload to hostile territory (exception: Amphibious Assault)</li>
                <li>Loading onto and/or offloading from a transport counts as a land unit’s entire move; it can’t move before loading or after offloading</li>
                <li>Bridging: A transport can load and offload units without moving from the friendly sea zone it’s in</li>
                <li>Land units belonging to friendly powers must load on their controller’s turn, be carried on your turn, and offload on a later turn of their controller</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Amphibious Assaults: </strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Can offload units to hostile territory from a friendly (or just made-friendly) sea zone</li>
                <li>If the sea zone could not be made friendly, the transport has to retreat</li>
                <li>Has to offload all units at once</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
{% endblock %}

